  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a8e51d5464cc",
  "content": "## Pre-Existing Foundations\n\n### Task 1: FallbackChunker\n\nThe simplest strategy — recursive separator cascade for unrecognized formats. Built first because the pipeline tests will use it as a real strategy.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_fallback.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs` (add module declaration)\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nCreate `crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_fallback.rs` with tests only:\n\n```rust\n//! FallbackChunker — recursive text splitting for unrecognized formats (D68).\n//!\n//! Splits text using a separator cascade: `\\n\\n` → `\\n` → ` ` → character-level.\n//! Produces chunks up to `max_tokens` using the chars/4 heuristic.\n\nuse corvia_common::errors::Result;\nuse crate::chunking_strategy::{ChunkingStrategy, ChunkMetadata, RawChunk, SourceMetadata};\n\npub struct FallbackChunker {\n    max_tokens: usize,\n}\n\nimpl FallbackChunker {\n    pub fn new(max_tokens: usize) -> Self {\n        Self { max_tokens }\n    }\n}\n\nimpl ChunkingStrategy for FallbackChunker {\n    fn name(&self) -> &str { \"fallback\" }\n    fn supported_extensions(&self) -> &[&str] { &[] }\n    fn chunk(&self, _source: &str, _meta: &SourceMetadata) -> Result<Vec<RawChunk>> {\n        todo!()\n    }\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    fn meta() -> SourceMetadata {\n        SourceMetadata {\n            file_path: \"readme.txt\".into(),\n            extension: \"txt\".into(),\n            language: None,\n            scope_id: \"test\".into(),\n            source_version: \"v1\".into(),\n        }\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_small_file_single_chunk() {\n        let chunker = FallbackChunker::new(512);\n        let source = \"Hello world.\\nThis is a test.\";\n        let chunks = chunker.chunk(source, &meta()).unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(chunks.len(), 1);\n        assert_eq!(chunks[0].content, source);",
